If you are not familiar with the 460 Rowland, it uses 45 ACP brass that is slightly longer than the regular 45ACP brass and will not chamber in the regular 45 ACP  barrel. The 45 will chamber and fire in the 460 Rowland barrel. The same magazines can be used for both 45 & 460 rounds. The bullet lengths are the same, just the 460 brass is longer and more power charge is loaded. This can all be researched on Youtube and that is what I did before undertaking this project.
If a trade is possible you would need to add a bit of cash. I have more pictures if you are interested.
 
The gun comes with two barrels, the 460 is in the gun. extra springs, Custom Grips and a pair of Magpul 1911 grips, custom lug wrench for the 460, about 250 rounds of 460 Rowland and 3 Magazines, and a zipper cover for the gun.
Asking $1200.00 cash
